news.title: Bengaluru: Consumer court orders BDA to refund ₹8 lakh for delay in handing over flat
news.para: On March 21, 2025, the Commission ordered BDA to refund Rs 8.03 lakh, along with an interest of 18% from the date the first payment was made, Rs 1 lakh for service deficiency, Rs 25,000 for mental agony, and another Rs 10,000 in litigation costs.

news.title: Start process to merge villages into Kolhapur civic body's limits: Maharashtra CM to officials
news.para: The discussion centred on the Kolhapur Municipal Corporation's recent proposal to merge 18 adjacent villages and two Maharashtra Industrial Development Corporations (MIDC) into the city limits.

news.title: Surat: 151 apartment residents get notices to vacate for lack of BU certificate
news.para: The multi-storey apartment buildings were not granted BUCs by the SMC due to non-compliance on various grounds, one of which is believed to be height.

news.title: Kerala: KCZMA ‘restriction’ causes concern among residents over property ownership & transfer rights
news.para: According to the pre-condition put forth by KCZMA for giving CRZ-2019 clearance for construction in these zones, the building should not be sold or transferred to non-traditional coastal communities.

news.title: Cabinet clears ₹150-crore plan for six new small airports in Bihar
news.para: The new airports will be developed in Madhubani, Birpur, Munger, Valmikinagar, Muzaffarpur and Saharsa, cabinet secretariat department additional chief secretary S Siddharth said after the cabinet meeting chaired by CM Nitish Kumar.

news.title: A 50% stamp duty concession for land transactions under MMRDA's Pen township project
news.para: The project will be implemented by the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) and Raigad Pen Growth Centre Ltd in Pen taluka.

news.title: Pune civic body pushes to relocate tenants of dilapidated wadas
news.para: Residents of structures found dangerous will be shifted to safer places during the rainy season and Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) will make necessary arrangements for the move.

news.title: MHADA invites bids to redevelop seven-acre PMGP Colony in Mumbai's Jogeshwari
news.para: The colony, originally constructed under the Prime Minister's Grant Project (PMGP), has remained in a dilapidated condition for many years, and this redevelopment marks a significant step towards addressing the long-standing housing concerns of residents.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Redevelopment of Rajaji Nagar nears completion
news.para: This phase includes a four-storey residential building costing Rs 9 crore, designed to accommodate 32 families in 2BHK apartments, each measuring 600 sq ft.

news.title: Odisha approves 43 housing projects under PMAY 2.0 in urban areas
news.para: Once completed, the 43 projects will provide 3,949 dwelling units to beneficiaries. These will be executed at a total cost of Rs 256 crores, with shares received from the Centre, state, and beneficiaries.

news.title: About ₹128 crore returned to over 350 homebuyers this year: UP-RERA
news.para: With this, UP Rera has, to date, transferred Rs 1,360 crore into the bank accounts of approximately 5,500 homebuyers who never received possession of their homes.

news.title: Supreme Court greenlights razing of 17 illegal buildings on private land in Thane
news.para: A partial working day bench of Justices Ujjal Bhuyan and Manmohan refused to stay the demolition order, pursuant to which Thane MC had demolished 8 buildings, on a plea by one Danish Zaheer Siddiqui, who claimed he had purchased a flat in those buildings.

news.title: Ahmedabad: AUDA approves hike in development fee for new projects
news.para: The proposal got the nod at its board meeting on Tuesday, paving the way for a 10-20-fold increase in the charges, which will directly impact the cost of residential, commercial, and other properties.

news.title: Blackstone’s Knowledge Realty Trust raises ₹1,400 crore in India's maiden REIT pre-IPO round
news.para: Knowledge Realty Trust (KRT), backed by Blackstone and Sattva Developers, raised ₹1,400 crore in a landmark pre-IPO placement. This marks India’s first such REIT fundraising, with participation from HNIs and family offices ahead of its ₹6,200 crore IPO.

news.title: Ahead of IPO, ArisInfra Solutions garners ₹225 crore from anchor investors
news.para: The nearly Rs 500-crore IPO will open for subscription on June 18 and conclude on June 20. The price band has been set at Rs 210 to Rs 222 per share for the public issue.

news.title: Delhi government considers mandatory water bill for property registration
news.para: According to sources, the government is considering Delhi Jal Board (DJB) reforms, and the water bill may become mandatory for property registration in Delhi.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves stamp duty concessions for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: An SPV has been established for the integrated redevelopment of Dharavi, one of the biggest slum sprawls in Asia which is located in central Mumbai.

news.title: Cement demand may be impacted in June due to early onset of monsoon: Ind-Ra
news.para: The cement volumes witnessed a "notable recovery of 10-11 per cent y-o-y" in the March 2025 quarter after recording a subdued 2 per cent growth in the first half of the last fiscal.

news.title: Homebuilder sentiment in USA skids to two and half years low in June: NAHB
news.para: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo Housing Market Index fell to 32, the lowest reading since December 2022, from 34 in May. Economists polled by Reuters had expected the sentiment score to improve to 36.

news.title: Sweden government plans to ease mortgage rules to help first-time buyers
news.para: Under the plan, people wanting a mortgage will be able to borrow up to 90% of the value of their property, up from the current 85%. A current requirement for the heaviest borrowers to pay back 3% of their loan each year will be dropped.
